The Header section of Dat54 sound entries contains base settings which can be used to manipulate a sound.

The section is used on most sound types to apply a category to a sound, which defines certain additional properties which can affect when and how they are played.

Settings in the Header section can be applied to each sound entry in a chain, with the preceeding sound's settings combining with the next one.

Fields:

Flags - flag value - Enables each variable indepedently. See table below.
Flags2 - flag value - Enables additional sound type behaviors.
Unk01 - ushort value - Max header size.
Volume - ushort value - negative values are represented as 65535 minus the amount to reduce.
VolumeVariance - ushort value
Pitch - ushort value - 100 = 1 semitone. Negative values are represented as 65535 minus the amount to reduce.
PitchVariance - ushort value
Pan - ushort value - 307 = left, 53 = right.
PanVariance - ushort value
PreDelay - ushort value - silence before sound in ms. Infinite = 65535
PreDelayVariance - ushort value
StartOffset - integer value - offset in ms. Infinite = 65535
StartOffsetVariance - integer value
AttackTime - ushort value - fade in time in ms.
ReleaseTime - ushort value - fade out time in ms.
DopplerFactor - ushort value - doppler intensity
Category - metahash - Adds additional filters.
LPFCutOff - ushort value - low pass filter cut-off 
LPFCutOffVariance - ushort value
HPFCutOff - ushort value - high pass filter cut-off
HPFCutOffVariance - ushort value
VolumeCurve - metahash - distance attenuation curves.
VolumeCurveScale - ushort value - dispersal rate of sound as it travels across a distance plane.
Unk19 - byte value - Unknown //EnvironmentalEffects?
Unk20 - byte value - Unknown //VirtualiseAsGroup - Stereo panning - L-R?
Unk21 - byte value - Unknown //DynamicPrepare?
UnkHash4 - metahash - Unknown - Curves/Variable?
UnkHash5 - metahash - Unknown - Curves/Variable?
Unk22 - float value - Echo. //x ?
Unk23 - float value - Echo. //y ?
Unk24 - float value - Echo. //z ?
Unk25 - float value - Unknown.
Unk26 - float value - Unknown.

//StartOffsetPercentage
//InvertPhase
//Mute
//MuteOnUserMusic

Flags:

The "Flags" value is used to enable any of the Header variables

The section reads "0xXXXXXXXX" where "X" represents the following digits in respective order:
0x00000001 - Flags2
0x00000002 - Unk01
0x00000004 - Volume
0x00000008 - VolumeVariance
0x00000010 - Pitch
0x00000020 - PitchVariance
0x00000040 - Pan
0x00000080 - PanVariance
0x00000100 - PreDelay
0x00000200 - PreDelayVariance
0x00000400 - StartOffset
0x00000800 - StartOffsetVariance
0x00001000 - AttackTime
0x00002000 - ReleaseTime
0x00004000 - DopplerFactor
0x00008000 - Category
0x00010000 - LPFCutOff
0X00020000 - HPFCutOff
0x00040000 - LPFCutOffVariance
0X00080000 - HPFCutOffVariance
0x00100000 - UnkHash3
0x00200000 - DistanceAttentuation
0x00400000 - Unk19
0x00800000 - Unk20
0x01000000 - Unk21
0x02000000 - UnkHash4
0x04000000 - UnkHash5
0x08000000 - Unk22
0x10000000 - Unk23
0x20000000 - Unk24
0x40000000 - Unk25
0x80000000 - Unk26

A = 2+8
B = 1+2+8
C = 4+8
D = 1+4+8
E = 2+4+8
F = 1+2+4+8

Flags2:

